# Intuition
BInary search on answer as we are trying all range of time that can give answer.

# Approach
- The prime problem of this question is to check whether the time is sufficient to run all computers simultaneously.
- for this the simple logic is that the battery time which is greater than or equal to the time(mid) we are checking we will assign computer to them for eg battery time=7, time(mid)=5 we can assign 1 computer to it directly and check for other batteries.
- The battery time less than time(mid), we will find average of these batteries and if average(total left battery time/no of computers left) is greater than or equal to time(mid) we can collectively assign these batteries to the remaining computers.
- batteries[]=[2,4,4,5,7]
computers=4;
checkTime(mid)=5;
for 5 and 7 battery time i.e. greater then 5(mid) so we will assign two computers, computers left=2.
the average of batteries left=10/2=5 i.e equal to checkTime(mid).
so this time can be a answer and save it and go find other maximum answer on the right.
- Range-->[1,1e14]
1e14 because 1 computer can use 1e5 batteres with each battery minutes 1e9 so total 1e5*1e9=1e14.


