# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Try to increase the minimum value in sub array of size $$n$$ containing batteries with longest duration from the heap of remaining battery hours by increasing them unit by unit.
Now minimum value in that sub array is our answer.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Sort the array in decreasing order.
2. Calculate sum of batteries from n to last index
3. Start from smallest value and try to make it equal to its next greatest by using battery hour obtained in step 02
4. Return minimum value from first n values and if there is extra battery hour reamaining with us then further distribute it among all computer

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(log(n))$$

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
$$O(1)$$


# Code
