2.Think about what the best answer would be?
This answer will never exceed **sum(batteries[i])/n** Why?
Because when the answer is equal to this value, it means that all batteries have been used up by the computer (even if there are remaining, there will be less than n power left).
3.**This value is the answer when no battery has more power than sum(batteries[i])/n.** Why?
