solutions.content:
# Intuition
In this question the first intuition that needs to come into the mind is that if x minutes is not the possible answer then there is no use in checking for >x minutes but if x minutes is possible then we can and should check for a higher time as thats what is required by the answer
The next and the main problem for this question is how to determine whether an answer is possible or not or whether we can run the computers simultaneously for a specific minutes :
   traverse the batteries array all the  batteries which have more than or equal the required minutes will be occupied for the whole duration and will suffice for one computer hence the remaining computers will be decreased by one,these batteries will not be available for swapping during the whole runtime,at the end of the traversal if the remaining computers are zero then the answer is possible , or if the batteries whose capacity is less than required have an average(on the basis of remaining computer) is greater or equal than the specified minutes then also the answer is possible

# Approach
Binary search on answers can be used for avoiding the linear search in the possible answers
Edit:-
The higher bound i have taken as one because the minimum possible computers are one and for that case the maximum possible answer is till all the batteries run out which is the sum of them

