# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We need to search a max time, till then all the batteries run simultaneusly. Keep in mind these 2 example:-
1. n=2, bat[]={3,3,3}, here after keeping the two laptops running we are left with one battery and can utilize, its power.
2. But, for n=3, bat[] = {3,5,10,10}, here we must first utilise the max batteries and use the lesser power batteries as spare batteries, so the max can be 8. Even 2 batteries are left with 2-2 all the 3 can't be kept on.

Using this way to check if our assumption of max time is true or not we can get required ans.   

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Assume the last 'n' batteries are utilised first, so the total of batteries before last n batteries to provide some extra power. Hence, find sum 0 to bat.size() -n-1.
2. Apply binary search on ans to get the desired ans.
3. As we have the sum of spare time(battery's power), we give it to every battery < assumed time, if at any moment we do not have enough battery time, the variable p will be < 0. 
4. We break at that point if p<0 , and go for lesser assumption, else if all batteries ran till assumed time, we take it as ans, and search for greater ans, if found ans gets updated.
5. Finally, return the ans.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(nlog(1e14) + nlog n ) including sorting.

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n) as we changed the original array.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    long long maxRunTime(int n, vector<int>& bat) {
        long long low=0 , high=1e14 , ans=0;
        sort(bat.begin() , bat.end());
        long long pre = 0;
        for(int i=0 ; i<bat.size()-n ; i++){
                pre += bat[i];
        }
        while(low<=high){
            long long mid = (low+high)/2; 
            int i;        
            long long p=pre;
            for(i=bat.size()-n ; i<bat.size() ; i++){

                p-=(mid-bat[i]);
                if(p<0) break;
            }
            if(i==bat.size()) low=mid+1 , ans=mid;
            else high = mid-1;
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

